Paper: hep-th/9505113

Date: 1995-05-18

Title: Spontaneous Magnetization in Lorentz Invariant Theories

Authors: D. Wesolowski and Y. Hosotani

Comments: 11 pages, latex, no figure. Note added. To appear in Phys Lett B

Journal-ref: Phys. Lett. B354 (1995) 396

In a class of three-dimensional Abelian gauge theories with both light andheavy fermions, heavy chiral fermions can trigger dynamical generation of amagnetic field, leading to the spontaneous breaking of the Lorentz invaiance.Finite masses of light fermions tend to restore the Lorentz invariance.